<h1>Rails Table Preferences Demo</h1>

<p>
  This demo screen uses in-memory rows for table display and the normal
  <code>table_preferences</code> table for preference persistence.
</p>

<p>
  It also seeds four preset types for the demo table:
  <code>owner-compact</code> (owner),
  <code>shared-baseline</code> (shared),
  <code>operations-default</code> (role),
  and <code>tokyo-default</code> (organization).
  The initial screen is resolved with
  <code>{ roles: [&quot;<%= @demo_scope_context[:roles].first %>&quot;], organization: &quot;<%= @demo_scope_context[:organization] %>&quot; }</code>
  so you can inspect role-default and organization-default availability alongside personal and shared examples.
</p>

<p>
  In that combined context, the role default still wins before the organization default,
  which matches the gem's normal default resolution order.
</p>

<p>
  To make the bundled preset API show the same role-scoped and organization-scoped presets in the selector,
  point <code>config.scope_context_method</code> at an application method that returns the same role and organization keys.
</p>

<p>
  The sample rows intentionally mix status, delivery date, amount range, and memo length
  so filter, sort, width, and preset changes are easier to spot without adding a full sample app.
</p>

<%= table_preferences_editor(
  table_key: :rails_table_preferences_demo_orders,
  settings: @table_preference_settings,
  columns: @table_columns,
  title: "デモ受注一覧の表示設定"
) %>

<%= form_with url: request.path, method: :get do %>
  <%= text_field_tag :search_word, params[:search_word], placeholder: "得意先名で絞り込み" %>

  <%= table_preferences_hidden_fields(
    settings: @table_preference_settings,
    columns: @table_columns
  ) %>

  <%= submit_tag "検索" %>
<% end %>

<%= table_preferences_table_tag(
  table_key: :rails_table_preferences_demo_orders,
  settings: @table_preference_settings,
  columns: @table_columns,
  class: "table"
) do %>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="order_no">受注番号</th>
      <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="customer_name">得意先名</th>
      <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="delivery_date">納品日</th>
      <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="status">状態</th>
      <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="amount">金額</th>
      <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="memo">備考</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <% @orders.each do |order| %>
      <tr>
        <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="order_no"><%= order[:order_no] %></td>
        <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="customer_name"><%= order[:customer_name] %></td>
        <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="delivery_date"><%= l(order[:delivery_date]) %></td>
        <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="status"><%= order[:status] %></td>
        <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="amount"><%= number_with_delimiter(order[:amount]) %></td>
        <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="memo"><%= order[:memo] %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
<% end %>